    Scientific Calculator

    web2.0calc.com online calculator provides\nbasic and advanced mathematical functions useful for school or\ncollege. You can operate the calculator directly from your keyboard,\nas well as using the buttons with your mouse. Become a fan!

    Quick Start Guide

    This guide will give you informative instructions on how to\nuse this calculator effectively.

    Chapter 1: Mouse Input

    Click the buttons to input a math formula or equation like\non a pocket calculator.

    Chapter 2: Keyboard Input

    If you prefer keyboard input of math formulas, you can type\ndirectly into the input bar. Pressing ↵ starts the calculation.

    Chapter 3: Functions

    To calculate a function like 'sine' with an argument like 90,\ninput the corresponding function name followed by the argument 90\nin parentheses. Example: sin(90)

    • Complex Numbers
      (2+2i)*(3+3i)\n
    • Integral Calculus
      int(x^2)\n
    • Differential Calculus
      diff(x^2)\n
    • Equations
      x^2+2x-1=9\n
    • Graphs
      plot(sin(x),x=0..360)\n

      (1, 2, 3)#(4, 5, 6)\n
